&TUTORIAL ------------ LIBRARYN - INTRODUCTION ------------------------ TUTORIAL
&NEXT SELECTION ===>%SELECT                             &
&
&                     -----------------------------------
                      |            LIBRARYN             |
                      |       GENERAL INTRODUCTION      |
                      -----------------------------------
$
  &LIBRARYN$ IS A MONSANTO-WRITTEN ADDITION TO THE STANDARD IBM SPF FUNCTIONS
  AND ALLOWS EASY ACCESS TO MODULES STORED ON LIBRARYN MASTER FILES. THE
  FACILITY DOES NOT AS YET INTERFACE WITH 'MOPP' BUT DOES LOG EACH ACCES TO A
  LIBRARYN MASTER AND ATTEMPTS TO PREVENT ACCIDENTAL CORRUPTION OF THE MASTER
  SUCH AS WOULD BE CAUSED BY TWO PEOPLE BOTH RETRIEVING THE SAME MODULE,
  ATTEMPTING TO ADD A MODULE WHICH ALREADY EXISTS ETC.

  THE FACILITY OFFERS FOUR BASIC OPTIONS:

  -&RETRIEVE$ (OPTION&1$) ALLOWS YOU TO EXTRACT A COPY OF A MODULE.
  -&REPLACE$  (OPTION&2$) RETURNS AN UPDATED MODULE TO THE LIBRARYN MASTER.
  -&INSERT$   (OPTION&3$) ADDS A NEW MODULE TO THE MASTER.
  -&INDXLIST$ (OPTION&4$) DISPLAYS BASIC CONTROL INFORMATION FOR A MODULE.

                           (CONTINUED ON NEXT PAGE)
<ACTION>
1 SELECT CHAR(36) CURSOR;
2 SELECT CHAR(8) LIST(' ') RETURN(' ');
3 * CHAR(8) INIT('ZTUTOR00');
4 * CHAR(8) INIT('ZTUTORR ');
5 * CHAR(8) INIT('ZTUTORG2');
<END>
